gomodel:SYNGO_5547  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Ablim1 (Actin-binding LIM protein 1) was identified as a PSD95 (DLG4, here the bait protein) interaction partner through tandem affinity purification (TAP) proteomics (Fig. 3, Table 1). This was validated by western blot; pulldown of endogenous Ablim1 using an antibody yields PSD95.. Experimental description: Figure 1: \"Generation of Tandem Affinity Purification (TAP)-tagged PSD-95 knockin mice\"\n\nAblim1 was detected by mass-spec, table 1, uniprot accession Q8K4G5\n\nantibody: rabbit Ablim1 (Abnova)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2023-11-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5547" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

